  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dd9\u0da7\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dc4\u0dcf \u0da9\u0dd3\u0dc3\u0dbd\u0dca \u0db7\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dba\u0dda \u0d9a\u0dd0\u0db4\u0dd3 \u0db4\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dd9\u0db1 \u0d85\u0da9\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A noticeable reduction in the use of petrol and diesel",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "With the introduction of the National Fuel Licence, there has been a noticeable reduction in fuel usage in the past three weeks.",
        "This is seen according to the data released by the Minister of Electricity and Energy Mr. Kanchana Wijesekera on his Twitter account.",
        "Accordingly, in the first three weeks of August, the use of petrol liters has dropped to 23.5, 22.1 and 21.0 million liters respectively.",
        "Likewise, the average daily use of petrol liters has dropped to 3.3, 3.1 and 3.0 million liters respectively in the last three weeks.",
        "Considering the situation regarding diesel, the usage rate increased in the second week of August compared to the first week, but it decreased again in the third week.",
        "Thus, the consumption of diesel liters in the first weeks was 13.0, 14.0 and 12.7 million liters respectively. Average daily usage was 1.8, 2.0 and 1.8 million litres.",
        "More than 6 million vehicles have been registered for the National Fuel License and with its introduction, the queues near the fuel stations became non-existent."
      ],
